  • Method Details

    • assign

      public org.objectweb.asm.tree.InsnList assign(IType input, IType output)
      This method determines whether a value of a type X can be converted to a value of a type Y, as is done during method invocations and variable assignments. Specifically, an assignment conversion is either a boxing conversion, an unboxing conversion, an identity conversion, an upcast, or a primitive coercion.
      Parameters:
      input - is the type of value that will be converted.
      output - is the type to convert the input value to.
      Returns:
      the bytecode that performs the actual conversion, or null, if no such conversion is possible.

    • unbox

      public org.objectweb.asm.tree.InsnList unbox(IType input, IType output)
      This method generates the bytecode necessary to perform an unboxing conversion.

      All Possible Unboxing Conversions

      java.lang.Character char
      java.lang.Byte byte
      java.lang.Short short
      java.lang.Integer int
      java.lang.Long long
      java.lang.Float float
      java.lang.Double double

      Parameters:

      output - is the type to convert the input value to.
      Returns:
      the bytecode that performs the actual conversion, or null, if no such conversion is possible.

    • sort

      public <T extends IInvokableMember> List<T> sort(Collection<T> members)
      This method sorts a collection of invokable members, using a topological sort, such that narrowest methods are closest the front of the resultant list.
      Parameters:
      members - are the invokable members to sort.
      Returns:
      the aforedescribed topologically sorted list.

    • checkArgs

      public <T extends IInvokableMember> List<T> checkArgs(List<T> members, List<? extends IType> arguments)
      Given the types of the arguments in an arguments-list and a set of invokable members, this method selects those invokable members whose formal-parameter types are acceptable matches for the given arguments.

      A method will be selected, if each argument X is convertible to the related formal-parameter type P, using an assignment conversion.

      Parameters:
      members - is the list invokable members to choose from.
      arguments - are the types of the arguments.
      Returns:
      a list containing the selected members.

    • select

      public <T extends IMember> List<T> select(IDeclaredType usage_site, Collection<T> members, boolean shared, String name)
      This method selects the accessible members of a type that have a given name.
      Parameters:
      usage_site - is the type from where the members are being accessed from.
      members - are the members to examine and possibly select.
      shared - is true, if and only if, the desired members are static.
      name - the name of the desired members.
      Returns:
      a list containing the selected members.

    • findFunctions

      The returned list is not sorted.

    • forceAssign

      public void forceAssign(org.objectweb.asm.tree.InsnList code, IExpressionType target, IReferenceType value)
      This method generates bytecode that assigns a reference-type to another, possibly primitive, type.

      If the target is a primitive-type, the generated code is a cast to the related boxed-type and then an unboxing operation.

      Parameters:
      code - is the code being generated.
      target - is the type of the assignee.
      value - is the type of the value being assigned to the assignee.
